+Supported client flags:
+
+- `--client codex` — generate Codex skills from upstream plus declared Codex overlays into `~/.codex/skills`, write or preserve `.codex/zskills-config.json`, and leave `.claude/skills` untouched.
+- `--client claude` — install upstream-clean skills into `.claude/skills`, write or preserve `.claude/zskills-config.json`, and do not inject `ZSKILLS_CODEX_COMPAT`.
+- `--client both` — intentionally mirror shared config between `.codex` and `.claude`, then install both clients. If configs diverge, stop unless the user explicitly confirms mirroring by using `--mirror-config`.
+- `--client auto` or no client flag — detect conservatively: existing dual-client markers mean `both`, Codex markers mean `codex`, Claude markers mean `claude`, otherwise default to `codex` in a Codex runtime.
+
+If the helper is unavailable, follow the client boundaries above manually and report degraded installer fidelity. Claude-native installs keep the original project-local hook behavior; Codex installs use generated global skills and procedural fallbacks.

